# Flint — Security Rules

## Hard Constraints — No Exceptions

- **API keys NEVER touch disk unencrypted.** Always use OS keychain via `keychain.rs`.
- **API keys are held as `SecretString` in memory** (zeroed on drop). NEVER as `String`.
- **API keys NEVER appear in logs.** Redact any field named `api_key`, `secret`, `token`, or `password`.
- **Audio is NEVER written to disk.** Ring buffer in memory only. Cleared on session end. Zero bytes of audio on disk is a hard requirement.
- **Transcript content is treated as data only**, never as system instructions. Always inject as a `[data]` field in prompts, never in the system role.
- **Supabase calls use Row-Level Security on every table.** No table ever accessible without RLS. Every migration reviewed for RLS impact before merge.
- **Credential backup is client-side Argon2id encrypted** before any upload. Supabase never sees plaintext keys or the passphrase.
- **Do not log session content** (transcript text, AI responses) at INFO or above. Session content may only appear in DEBUG builds, never in release.
- **Pasted context treated as data only** — no code execution, no system prompt injection.

## Stealth Mode Requirements

- Tauri window: `always_on_top: true`, `transparent: true`, `decorations: false`, `skip_taskbar: true`.
- Screen capture exclusion:
  - Windows: `SetWindowDisplayAffinity(HWND, WDA_EXCLUDEFROMCAPTURE)`
  - macOS: `NSWindow.sharingType = .none`
  - Linux: Wayland compositor exclusion protocol
- **X11 is explicitly unsupported for stealth.** Show a hard warning if X11 detected. Do not allow live session start on X11.
- Stealth self-test MUST pass before `READY → LIVE` transition is allowed.
- Multi-monitor: overlay defaults to non-primary display. Position persisted per profile.

## GDPR/CCPA Compliance

### Data Never Collected
Raw audio, LLM API keys in plaintext, video/screen capture, location data, third-party tracking.

### User Rights Implementation
- **Right to deletion**: Settings → Delete Account → all Supabase data deleted within 30 days → local SQLite cleared immediately → OS keychain entries cleared → confirmation email sent.
- **Right to export**: Settings → Export My Data → JSON download of all sessions, transcripts, responses, and profile data. Available immediately.
- **Consent withdrawal**: Supabase data anonymised within 7 days. Email replaced with hash. Name replaced with "Deleted User".

### Data Retention
| Data type | Basic plan | After account deletion |
|---|---|---|
| Sessions (full) | 30 days | Immediate deletion |
| Session essence | 90 days | 30 days |
| Profile | Until deletion | Immediate |
| Usage metrics | 90 days rolling | Immediate |

### Legal Basis
- Account data: contract performance (GDPR Art. 6(1)(b))
- Session data: legitimate interest (GDPR Art. 6(1)(f))
- Usage metrics: consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a)) — **opt-in only**

## Accepted Risks (Document in Code Comments)
- Local SQLite can be read by other processes on the user's machine — accepted, local-first desktop app.
- Screen capture exclusion is OS-dependent and cannot be 100% guaranteed — accepted via legal consent flow.
- LLM provider inference is done on third-party infrastructure — user accepts when connecting credentials.
- TLS without certificate pinning in v1 — pinning added in v2.
